/ Gives you control of your own virtual resources
/ Logically isolated from other VPCs
/ When you create a VPC you must give it a CIDR block. The largest is /16 and the smallest is /28
 * CIDR (a range of small IP addresses)
 
 / Elastic Network Interface
 * You cannot detach a primary elastic network interface
 
 /Route tables - each subnet must be associated with a route table. The mapping is 1:1
